Virgil, I think, tells us, that when the Mob are assembled in a riotous and tumultuous Manner, and all Sorts of missible Weapons fly about, if a Man of Gravity and Authority appears amongst them, the Tumult is presently appeased, and the Mob, which when collected into one Body, may be well compared to an Ass, erect their long Ears at the grave Man's Discourse.
On the contrary, when a Set of grave Men and Philosophers are disputing; when Wisdom herself may in a Manner be considered as present, and administering Arguments to the Disputants, should a Tumult arise among the Mob, or should one Scold who is Wisdom herself equal in Noise to a mighty Mob, appear among the said Philosophers; Philosophers Disputes cease in a Moment, Wisdom no longer performs Wisdom herself ministerial Office, and the Attention of every one is immediately attracted by the Scold alone.
